<TITLE> Dozens feared killed in Dantewada Maoist attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, May 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - At least 20 people, including policemen, were feared killed when suspected Maoist rebels detonated a landmine under a bus in Chhattisgarh on Monday, local media reported. Television news channels said at least 20-25 were killed, and one report said up to 50 people could have been killed. The attack occurred in Dantewada, said to be the worst hit by the four-decades-old insurgency that has killed thousands of people and has been described by the government as India's gravest internal security threat. 
